		<div class="blog-header">
			<h2 class="blog-title">
					<a class="blog-title-link blog-link" href="//www.mannywaks.com/blog/president-of-the-jewish-federation-of-sao-paulo-responds-to-serious-allegations-and-my-response">President of the Jewish Federation of Sao Paulo responds to serious allegations, and my response</a>

			</h2>
			<p class="blog-date">
					<span class="date-text">
		30/4/2018
	</span>

			</p>
			<p class="blog-comments">
					<a href="//www.mannywaks.com/blog/president-of-the-jewish-federation-of-sao-paulo-responds-to-serious-allegations-and-my-response#comments" class="blog-link">
		0 Comments
	</a>

			</p>
		</div>
	
		<div class="blog-separator">&nbsp;</div>
	
		<div class="blog-content">
				<span class="imgPusher" style="float:left;height:80px"></span><span style="display: table;width:auto;position:relative;float:left;max-width:100%;;clear:left;margin-top:20px;*margin-top:40px"><a><img src="/uploads/4/7/1/9/4719581/letter-from-sao-paulo-federation-president_orig.jpg" style="margin-top: 5px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 10px; border-width:1px;padding:3px; max-width:100%" alt="Picture" class="galleryImageBorder wsite-image"></a><span style="display: table-caption; caption-side: bottom; font-size: 90%; margin-top: -10px; margin-bottom: 10px; text-align: center;" class="wsite-caption"></span></span> <div class="paragraph" style="display:block;">​The President of the Jewish Federation of Sao Paulo, Mr Luiz Kignel, has responded to my blog post from 28 March 2018&nbsp; titled <a href="http://www.mannywaks.com/blog/brazil-jewish-community-appalling-response-by-the-sao-paulo-leadership-to-violence-relating-to-allegations-of-child-sexual-abuse-cover-ups-and-intimidation" target="_blank"><font color="#5848b7">Brazil Jewish community - appalling response by the Sao Paulo leadership to violence relating to allegations of child sexual abuse, cover-ups and intimidation</font></a> (my brief email response to him is below his letter):<br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br>​<br><br><br></div> <hr style="width:100%;clear:both;visibility:hidden;">  <span class="imgPusher" style="float:right;height:0px"></span><span style="display: table;width:auto;position:relative;float:right;max-width:100%;;clear:right;margin-top:0px;*margin-top:0px"><a><img src="/uploads/4/7/1/9/4719581/luiz-kignel_1_orig.jpg" style="margin-top: 5px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 10px; border-width:1px;padding:3px; max-width:100%" alt="Picture" class="galleryImageBorder wsite-image"></a><span style="display: table-caption; caption-side: bottom; font-size: 90%; margin-top: -10px; margin-bottom: 10px; text-align: center;" class="wsite-caption">Mr Luiz Kignel</span></span> <div class="paragraph" style="display:block;"><strong>​My email response (dated 29 April 2018):</strong><br><br><span>Dear Mr Kignel,</span><br><br><span>I confirm receipt of your letter, which you have also circulated widely.</span><br><br><span>Briefly, in response, you assert that what I wrote on 28 March 2018 in a blogpost is a lie. You make no genuine attempt to refute the allegations. Repeatedly stating that something is a lie, does not make it one. I’d encourage you to outline what you believe are the lies, and I’ll happily publicly publish your version of events.</span><br><br><span>I should note that you were personally invited to meet with me during my recent visit to Sao Paulo. You received a WhatsApp message on 27 February 2018. Indeed, I met many of your colleagues when I was there. So, we did reach out to you, and you seem to have chosen to deliberately ignore this invitation.</span><br><br><span>Let me assure you that I fully stand behind what I have written. At the same time, I’m willing to engage with you and your colleagues in good faith to try to rectify the situation. While I do not have any additional trip planned for Sao Paulo, if you’d like me to consider such a trip to try to resolve this matter (as per your invitation), I’d be willing to discuss with you the possibility of another such visit.</span><br><br><span>At this stage, I’m not in a position to share additional details, as there are a number of factors preventing me from doing so. I will, however, do so in due course.</span><br><br><span>In the meantime, I wish you all the best, especially in appropriately addressing the issue of child sexual abuse in your local Jewish community. And of course I'm happy to assist where I can.</span><br><br><span>Regards,</span><br><span>​</span><br><span>Manny Waks</span><br><span>Chief Executive Officer</span><br><span><a href="http://www.kolvoz.org/" target="_blank">Kol v'Oz</a></span></div> <hr style="width:100%;clear:both;visibility:hidden;">

		</div>
	
	
